msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.103:0.2"
msgid "10. Ānisaṃsavagga "
msgstr "10. Benefit "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.103:0.3"
msgid "103. Ukkhittāsikasutta "
msgstr "103. With a Drawn Sword "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.444, sc1
msgctxt "an6.103:1.1"
msgid "“Cha, bhikkhave, ānisaṃse sampassamānena alameva bhikkhunā sabbasaṅkhāresu anodhiṃ karitvā dukkhasaññaṃ upaṭṭhāpetuṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, seeing six benefits is quite enough to establish the perception of suffering in all conditions without qualification. "

msgctxt "an6.103:1.2"
msgid "Katame cha? "
msgstr "What six? "

# NOTE: At SN 35.238 the killer with ukkhittasika threatens to chop off a head, so sword fits better than dagger.
msgctxt "an6.103:1.3"
msgid "‘Sabbasaṅkhāresu ca me nibbidasaññā paccupaṭṭhitā bhavissati, seyyathāpi ukkhittāsike vadhake. "
msgstr "‘Perception of disillusionment will be established in me for all conditions, like a killer with a drawn sword.’ "

#. VAR: gacchissanti → gacchanti (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an6.103:1.4"
msgid "Sabbalokā ca me mano vuṭṭhahissati, nibbāne ca santadassāvī bhavissāmi, anusayā ca me samugghātaṃ gacchissanti, kiccakārī ca bhavissāmi, satthā ca me pariciṇṇo bhavissati mettāvatāyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘My mind will rise above the whole world.’ ‘I will see extinguishment as peaceful.’ ‘My underlying tendencies will be uprooted.’ ‘I will fulfill my duty.’ ‘I will have served my Teacher with love.’ "

msgctxt "an6.103:1.5"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cha ānisaṃse sampassamānena alameva bhikkhunā sabbasaṅkhāresu anodhiṃ karitvā dukkhasaññaṃ upaṭṭhāpetun”ti. "
msgstr "Seeing these six benefits is quite enough to establish the perception of suffering in all conditions without qualification.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.103:1.6"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

